SIMPLE: overlook
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overlook
<hw>O`ver*look"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Overlooked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overlooking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To look
down upon from a place that is over or above; to look over or view from
a higher position; to be situated above, so as to command a view of;
<as>as, to <ex>overlook</ex> a valley from a hill; a hotel room that
<ex>overlooks</ex> the marketplace</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The pile
<xex>o'erlooked</xex> the town.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Titan] with burning eye did hotly <qex>overlook</qex> them.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: To supervise; to watch over; sometimes, to
observe secretly; <as>as, to <ex>overlook</ex> a gang of laborers; to
<ex>overlook</ex> one who is writing a letter.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To inspect; to examine; to look over carefully or
repeatedly.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Overlook</xex> this pedigree.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The time and care that are required⟦br⟧
To <qex>overlook</qex> and file and polish well.</q>
<rj><qau>Roscommon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To look upon with an evil eye; to bewitch by looking
upon; to fascinate.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If you trouble me I will <qex>overlook</qex> you, and then your
pigs will die.</q> <rj><qau>C. Kingsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To look over and beyond (anything) without seeing
it; to miss or omit in looking; to fail to notice; to fail to observe;
<as>as, to <ex>overlook</ex> a mistake in addition; to <ex>overlook</ex>
a missing bolt</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>To refrain from bestowing
notice or attention upon; to disregard or deliberately ignore; to pass
over without censure or punishment; to excuse or pardon (a fault, error,
or misdeed).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>The times of ignorance therefore God <qex>overlooked</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts xvii. 30 (Rev. Ver. )</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They <qex>overlook</qex> truth in the judgments they pass.</q>
<rj><qau>Atterbury.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The pardoning and <qex>overlooking</qex> of faults.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overlooker</ent>⟦br⟧
